introduced something new with AppleScript.

00:42:26.030 --> 00:42:29.000
It's called AppleScript Cocoa or AppleScript Objective-C.

00:42:29.000 --> 00:42:33.380
It's got a couple different names
but basically within this environment

00:42:33.380 --> 00:42:38.829
and within Xcode AppleScript can call any
Cocoa framework call that you want to make

00:42:38.829 --> 00:42:43.389
at all directly from within the language, so.

00:42:46.230 --> 00:42:52.469
[Applause] So not only can you call the shell using the
do shell script command, now you can just get straight

00:42:52.469 --> 00:42:56.769
at any Cocoa call that you to do, anything
Objective-C can get at we can get at with here.

00:42:56.769 --> 00:43:02.679
So you can combine these as a way to
extend your abilities using Services.

00:43:02.679 --> 00:43:06.569
